HEADWORD: Urinator
<hw>U"ri*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from
<ets>urinari</ets> to plunge under water, to dive.]</ety> <def>One who
dives under water in search of something, as for pearls; a diver.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

